==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sprite
<hw>Sprite</hw> <pr>(spr⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sprit</ets>, F. <ets>esprit</ets>, fr. L. <ets>spiritus</ets>. See
<er>Spirit</er>, and cf. <er>Sprightly</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
spirit; a soul; a shade; also, an apparition. See
<er>Spright</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gaping graves received the wandering, guilty
<qex>sprite</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An elf; a fairy; a goblin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The green woodpecker, or
yaffle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spritely</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Spriteliness</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Spritefully</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Spriteful</ent>⟦br⟧
